    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bindings of a style originating in France in the late 17th century characterized by outside covers of austere plainness and elaborate doublures or inside covers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000000401/Carter, ABC for Book Collectors (1972)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Banden in een stijl die zijn oorsprong vindt in het laat-zeventiende eeuwse Frankrijk, gekarakteriseerd door bijzonder sobere buitenbanden en rijk versierde binnenbanden of beleggen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
